Question: join multiple iterators in java: :Does anybody know how to join multiple iterators in Java? The solution I found iterate through one iterator first, and then move on to the next one. However, what I want is when next() gets called, it first returns the first element from the first iterator. Next time when next() gets called, it returns the first element from the second iterator, and so on.Thanks
Please using this api: Iterator.next.
Answer: <<<api>>>: Iterator.next
<<<code>>>: 
Iterator<String> iterator1 = list1.iterator();
Iterator<String> iterator2 = list2.iterator();
Iterator<String> iterator3 = list3.iterator();

List<Iterator<String>> iterators = new ArrayList<>();
iterators.add(iterator1);
iterators.add(iterator2);
iterators.add(iterator3);

Iterator<String> combinedIterator = new Iterator<String>() {
    int currentIteratorIndex = 0;

    @Override
    public boolean hasNext() {
        while (currentIteratorIndex < iterators.size() && !iterators.get(currentIteratorIndex).hasNext()) {
            currentIteratorIndex++;
        }
        return currentIteratorIndex < iterators.size();
    }

    @Override
    public String next() {
        if (!hasNext()) {
            throw new NoSuchElementException();
        }
        return iterators.get(currentIteratorIndex).next();
    }

    @Override
    public void remove() {
        throw new UnsupportedOperationException();
    }
};
<<<explanation>>>: 
This code creates a new Iterator that cycles through the elements of the iterators in the list. It does this by keeping track of the current iterator index and incrementing it whenever the current iterator has no more elements. The next method simply returns the next element from the current iterator.

The hasNext method checks if the current iterator has any more elements. If it does, it returns true. If it doesn't, it increments the current iterator index and checks the next iterator. This continues until it finds an iterator with more elements or until it has checked all iterators. If it has checked all iterators and none of them have any more elements, it returns false.

The remove method is not supported because it is not necessary for this operation.
